sub_title: PhD Candidate | Fostering a (Food System)Transition by Design | TU Delft
summary: I am a charismatic designer, researcher and student coach in the fields of systemic design, designing for transitions, and food and eating design. I believe design brings valuable capabilities for addressing complex challenges and system transitions. However, there is still a lot to explore regarding how to design for or foster system transitions. This exploration space inspires my research. My interests and expertise in this area include systems thinking, envisioning alternative futures, conflict resolution through integrative thinking, and design as a way to foster behavioural change. Outside of my research, I am also passionate about exploring how design can influence people to experience daily life in unexpected, playful, and positive ways.
